I have been using multiband compression in just about every mix lately. I love using it to balance out vocals. Add a band to the lower frequencies to control plosives or any low end build up. Add a band to the mids to to control harshness (if it's present) and add a band to the top end to control sibilance just like a DeEsser would. It only engages when the signal passes the threshold you set. Compared to EQ which is static. *
